The paper discusses the use of Decoy Routing as an anti-censorship technique, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the placement of Decoy Routers in the Internet, which involves network infrastructure and routing protocols, making it relevant to the categories of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also considers the impact of Decoy Routing on censorship and surveillance, which falls under the category of cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
